summary:

Adobe is a strong company, but there are still risk factors that could lead to continued turbulence for the stock.", "As we open the curtain to a new year, the following four cryptocurrencies stand out as having the potential to triple your money in 2023.
AvalancheWhen it comes to innovation and tangible results, Ethereum (CRYPTO: ETH) tends to lead the pack.
AlgorandThe second cryptocurrency capable of delivering 200% returns to investors in 2023, if things go its way, is Algorand (CRYPTO: ALGO).
IOTAA third cryptocurrency that has the potential to triple your money in 2023 -- and that's certainly off the radar when compared to Avalanche and Algorand -- is IOTA (CRYPTO: MIOTA).
StellarThe fourth and final cryptocurrency that can triple your money in 2023 is Stellar (CRYPTO: XLM).", "Tulsa King Season 1 Episode 8 offers more of what we've come to expect -- moving chess pieces around on a board while we wait for something to happen.
So far, Tulsa King has been a lot more buildup than actual storytelling.
Dwight needs Tyson, and the less Tyson knows about the business, the more helpful he'll be in the long run.
But he does inspire people, and the showdown coming on the Tulsa King Season 1 finale (already??)
Hopefully, Tulsa King Season 2 will be less world-building and more plain fun, but it could be Dwight's journey to continuously build to something that might never come to fruition."]

Oil Stocks To Buy [Or Avoid] In January 2023Occidental Petroleum (OXY Stock)Leading off, Occidental Petroleum Corporation (OXY) is an American multinational oil and gas exploration and production company.', 'Adobe has launched the free Enhance Speech service, which uses a special AI algorithm to cleanse speech recordings of extraneous noise and improve sound quality.

According to Adobe, the featured service is capable of taking recordings made with an average microphone to the point where they sound like they were recorded in a professional studio.

In each review, influencers were asked to provide a one to five rating on their overall experience working with the brand, with five being the highest and one being the lowest.
Positive reviews were defined as those with an overall rating of four or five, whereas negative reviews had ratings of one or two.
Influencers are required to have collaborated with a brand before reviewing it on the platform.', 'Internet browsers will shift from generalized to specializedAs web apps, communal browsing, and decentralized technology continue to grow, browsers have become too generalized and antiquated for the future of web apps.
Web apps offer virality and infinite possibilities for product-led growth, and are finally powerful enough for sophisticated apps like Photoshop.
Browsers will be reimagined for collaboration and higher performance web apps ‚Äî like Arc from The Browser Company.
As a result, the value of creative work will shift from outcomes to process and ingenuity.
Content creators will own their audience and some will become "platform-less"Content creators with mass audiences are seeking novel ways to own the relationship.']

We assume companies with shrinking free cash flow will slow their rate of shrinkage, and that companies with growing free cash flow will see their growth rate slow, over this period.
For a number of reasons a very conservative growth rate is used that cannot exceed that of a country's GDP growth.
In this case we have used the 5-year average of the 10-year government bond yield (2.0%) to estimate future growth.
The Simply Wall St app conducts a discounted cash flow valuation for every stock on the NASDAQGS every day."]
